programme.desc: KAOS devises a chemical that wipes out 90 percent of the US potato crop. While flying to Idaho, Max becomes convinced that he keeps seeing the Red Baron, but 99 and the Chief never see him.

programme.title: Get Smart
programme.desc: Max is assigned to protect Control courier Busby during a plane ride, but he mysteriously disappears from the bathroom in mid-flight.

programme.title: Get Smart
programme.desc: Dying mobster Sam Vittorio will only reveal the location of his hidden loot to his proteges, Connie and Floyd, who look remarkably like Max and 99. Using appearance to their advantage, they visit Sam.

programme.title: Get Smart
programme.sub-title: Diamonds Are A Spy's Best Friend
programme.desc: While buying 99's engagement ring, Max unknowingly stumbles on a robbery and receives a huge diamond from Mr Spiegel to keep it out of the thieves' hands.

programme.title: Get Smart
programme.desc: As soon as Max asks someone to be his best man, they get killed or injured. The Chief orders Max to make indestructible Hymie his best man. This falls right into KAOS plans to ruin Max's bachelor party.

programme.title: Get Smart
programme.sub-title: The Return Of The Ancient Mariner
programme.desc: CONTROL is on a high-security alert as The Chameleon, another KAOS master of disguise, is on the loose. He plans to kidnap Admiral Hargrade and take his place at a top-secret conference.

programme.title: Get Smart
programme.desc: The day before his wedding, Max meets Dr Madre, who has a KAOS map to a uranium mine. Max unknowingly drinks the map, which will appear on his chest, but only if he remains standing for 48 hours.

programme.title: Get Smart
programme.desc: Max goes to a Hong Kong tailor (Hong Kong Tailors - We Duplicate Anything!) to pick up a new secret weapon, but all the tailor gives him is a blue blazer. To make matters worse, it's not even Max's size.

programme.title: Get Smart
programme.desc: While Max and the Chief are involved in a gunfight with KAOS, 99 is preparing dinner at home for Max. While being domestic, she spends time talking with her new neighbour, Naomi Farkas.

programme.title: Get Smart
programme.desc: Max and 99 are about to leave on their honeymoon when he gets a telegram calling him to duty in the Navy. He rushes to the office to get the Chief to intercede but the Chief has been called up too.

programme.title: Get Smart
programme.desc: Max arrives at a bus station locker and receives his orders from a self-destructing tape recorder, a la Mission: Impossible. The tape recorder explodes, destroying everything but the tape.

programme.title: Get Smart
programme.desc: While sailing on their honeymoon, Max blows up the boat, marooning the couple on a deserted island. While trying to stay alive on the island, they can't find any food, but they do find footprints.

programme.title: Get Smart
programme.desc: CONTROL receives word that KAOS scientist Dr Canyon has invented an invisibility spray and wants to defect with it. Coupled with that is the news that KAOS has stolen the Ginsberg Papers.

programme.title: Get Smart
programme.desc: KAOS is using a new play to pass information on to its agents, though CONTROL can't figure out how. To penetrate the cast, Max and 99 take acting instruction, but it doesn't seem to sink in for Max.

programme.title: Get Smart
programme.sub-title: The Day They Raided The Knights
programme.desc: A computer orders 99 laid off when budget cuts hit CONTROL. She goes to work at Knights Stamp Redemption Centre, while Max and the Chief search for the new KAOS munitions depot.

programme.title: Get Smart
programme.desc: Control agent Esperanza manages to get The Tequila Mockingbird away from Kaos, but she's killed before she can reveal its location. Max and 99 are sent to Mexico to find it and keep it out of Kaos clutches.

programme.title: Get Smart
programme.desc: KAOS has been blowing up space centres every time they test a new missile. Every base destroyed has been next to a golf course, and Chuck Cramer has been the golf pro at every club.

programme.title: Get Smart
programme.desc: The Chief takes up computer dating and winds up dating a gorgeous young woman. Ordered to follow the Chief, Max and 99 try to break up that romance while convincing the Chief to date 99's mother.

programme.title: Get Smart
programme.desc: Max's resemblance to the King of Coronia is needed as the king is endangered by rotten, ruthless Rupert of Rathskeller. The two switch identities, and the king moves in with Max and 99.

programme.title: Get Smart
programme.desc: Agent 86 gets jealous over 99 accidentally kissing King Charles and so he pretends to be the king, only 99 realises it, so she pretends that she likes the king and not Max.

programme.title: Get Smart
programme.desc: KAOS has been hijacking trucks filled with electronic equipment, so Max goes undercover as a truck driver.

programme.title: Get Smart
programme.desc: Wheelchair-bound mastermind Leadside is caught in a robbery by Max and announces a three-part plan. Phase one, he will escape from Max. Phase two, he will destroy CONTROL. Phase three, he will kill Maxwell Smart.

programme.title: Get Smart
programme.desc: CONTROL corners a KAOS agent in a house and attempts to take him alive, but he manages to shoot Max in the buttocks.

programme.title: Get Smart
programme.desc: Max is assigned to see Agent Kendall safely off to Europe, however, he mysteriously disappears from the airport. When Max and the Chief go to find out what happened, the Chief also disappears.

programme.title: Get Smart
programme.desc: With the Chief gone, Max appoints himself temporary chief and decides to get kidnapped to find out where missing agents are going.

programme.title: Get Smart
programme.desc: Max fills in at spy school for an afternoon and is forced to deal with two students whose grades are alarming.

programme.title: Get Smart
programme.desc: While trying to rescue Professor Pheasant from a nuclear prison, 99 tells Max she's pregnant. Max gets so excited he tells a reporter that he's a spy and blows his cover.

programme.title: Get Smart
programme.desc: KAOS is taken over by Ironhand, who, oddly enough, has an iron hand. Ironhand tries to steel the AAAMM (The Anti-anti-anti-missile missile) plans, which 99 is transporting in an armed baby buggy.

programme.title: Get Smart
programme.desc: KAOS is smuggling in a secret formula for an explosive that they will use to blow up California. They trace the smugglers to Miss Valerie's School for Expectant Fathers, which Max and the Chief enrol in.

programme.title: Get Smart
programme.desc: The Chief orders Max to marry Ann Cameron, a widow who marries agents and then kills them. Forced to romance Ann on the night of his wedding anniversary, Max receives a lot of grief from 99 over the assignment.

programme.title: Get Smart
programme.sub-title: The Treasure Of C. Errol Madre
programme.desc: Max and Larabee are delivering CONTROL's payroll to the bank when KAOS manages to hijack it.

programme.title: Get Smart
programme.desc: KAOS Agent Bohrman is carrying their new code book strapped to his chest, and Max is assigned to replace it with a fake code book.

programme.title: Get Smart
programme.desc: Max is nervous as he waits for 99 to give birth. At the same time, CONTROL is desperately trying to find the new KAOS HQ.

programme.title: Get Smart
programme.desc: Simon the Likable is coming to town to steal the Huffiker Plans from the Pentagon. Simon is unstoppable because everyone that sees him instantly likes him and will do anything for him.

programme.title: Get Smart
programme.desc: CONTROL is transporting vicious killer Big Eddie Little to jail by pretending to run in a marathon with him. Little breaks away from Max, but not before Max shoots him in the shoulder.

programme.title: Get Smart
programme.desc: CONTROL agents are receiving bananas in the mail and then being murdered. KAOS is using Chucko, an ape made to look like a human and currently working as CONTROL agent Armstrong.

programme.title: Get Smart
programme.desc: Max goes to meet CONTROL Agent Carruthers and finds him dying of old age. The problem is that Carruthers is only 28 years old. More and more agents are rapidly ageing and dying, thanks to a new invention by KAOS.

programme.title: Get Smart
programme.desc: Everyone important in Washington suffers bad dreams and the president orders CONTROL to discover why.

programme.title: Get Smart
programme.desc: The planet is being frozen by a giant KAOS fan in the North Pole. Max gets snowed in, so 99 and CIA agent Quigley journey to the North Pole to find Mounties Siegfried and Shtarker.

programme.title: Get Smart
programme.desc: The Chief worries that living with Max has made 99 clumsy, but she convinces the Chief to give her another assignment. He sends her undercover to a radio show which KAOS is using to send information.

programme.title: Get Smart
programme.desc: Max and 99 are in London when Jack the Ripper tries to kill 99. Max kills Jack, only to find that he is a wax figure brought to life. They join Inspector Sparrow in infiltrating Duval's House of Wax.

programme.title: Get Smart
programme.desc: Max goes undercover as Hitler to infiltrate Duval's House of Wax, which is bringing wax figures to life.

programme.title: Get Smart
programme.desc: Max is serving as a courier on an airplane when he is forced to release the package from the plane. It lands on the roof of a man's mansion who hasn't allowed visitors in to his house in 20 years.

programme.title: Get Smart
programme.desc: Six CONTROL agents are killed and the common denominator is that they all played on the CONTROL training school's baseball team.

programme.title: Get Smart
programme.desc: A KAOS defector agrees to testify for CONTROL, so KAOS sends the Exterminator, the most cold-blooded, calculating killer who ever worked for KAOS, to kill him.

programme.title: Get Smart
programme.desc: Dr Harper dies, leaving the only sample of his rocket fuel behind and KAOS finds it first. Max and 99 have to pose as a valet and maid at the Bulmanian Embassy to recover stolen rocket fuel.

programme.desc: KAOS kidnaps 99 and replaces her with an impostor. The real 99 is held prisoner while the fake 99 keeps feeding Max poisoned meals. The real 99 escapes to try and save Max.

programme.desc: The Roman Bath Spas are being used by KAOS to sweat secrets out of people by using truth serum.

programme.desc: Mike Sheahan is one of the most respected AFL journalists in the history of the game. Take a trip down memory lane with the best interviews and stories in Open Mike Top 30.

programme.title: AFL: R13 WB v HAW
programme.desc: We're at Marvel Stadium ahead of Western Bulldogs v Hawthorn. Plus all the teams for round 13.

programme.title: AFL: R13 ADE v BRI
programme.desc: Two flag contenders with a recent history of close encounters look to solidify their places in the top four.

programme.title: AFL: R13 RIC v SYD
programme.desc: All eyes on coach Dean Cox and the Swans as they travel back to the MCG in desperate need of a win.

programme.title: AFL: Best of Bounce
programme.desc: Check out the best moments from Bounce's Yesterday's Heroes Challenges in 2025.

programme.title: AFL: Best of Bounce
programme.desc: Check out the best moments from Bounce's Yesterday's Heroes Challenges in 2025.

programme.title: Best Games Ever: 1994 PF GEE V NM
programme.desc: 1994 Preliminary Final. The Roos and the Cats face off for a spot in the 1994 Grand Final. The game rests on Mick Martyn v Gary Ablett Senior in a match that goes right down to the wire.

programme.title: Best Games Ever: 1994 R7 SYD v STK
programme.desc: 1994 Round 7. The Swans and the Saints go at it in a see-sawing clash way back in 1994. The game's greatest goalkicker - Tony Lockett - has a game for the ages as he tries to drag his Saints over the line.

programme.title: Best Games Ever: 1996 PF SYD v ESS
programme.desc: 1996 Preliminary Final. A Grand Final spot is on the line when the Bombers head to the SCG to take on the Swans. A brutal game that goes right down to the wire.

programme.title: Best Games Ever: 1986 EF FIT v ESS
programme.desc: 1986 Elimination Final. Fitzroy's last finals series before merging with Brisbane, the Roy Boys put on a farewell show for the ages against Bombers in front of 60,000 fans.

programme.title: Best Games Ever: 2004 R11 ESS v HAW
programme.desc: 2004, Round 11. Essendon and the Hawks have hated each other for generations. But the now infamous 'Line in the Sand' game would stoke the fire for years to come. This is unrelenting, unapologetic, unsociable footy.

programme.title: Best Games Ever: 1977 GF NM v COL
programme.desc: 1977 Grand Final. The Roos and the Pies play out one of the most memorable Grand Finals in history.

programme.title: Best Games Ever: 1998 R22 NM v WB
programme.desc: 1998, Round 22. The 'King' Wayne Carey is arguably the best to have ever played - and he shows us why in this game against the Dogs, in a last quarter that has to be seen to be believed.

programme.title: Best Games Ever: 2013 R19 PA v ADE
programme.desc: 2013, Round 19. The Showdowns between Adelaide and Port Adelaide are essential viewing every year, but this one is right up there with the best, including a goal - and a finish - that lived on long after the final siren.

programme.title: Best Games Ever: 1979 GF CAR v COL
programme.desc: 1979 Grand Final. Any time you get the Pies and the Blues in a big game you can bet there will be fireworks, but throw them both into a Grand Final and you get something else entirely.

programme.title: Best Games Ever: 2000 R21 FRE v WCE
programme.desc: 2000 Round 21. The WA Derby looks a fizzer when the Eagles go 42 points up, until Dale Kickett fires up and the Dockers start to close the gap, and fast.

programme.title: Best Games Ever: 1993 SOO SA v VIC
programme.desc: 1993 State Of Origin. Probably the best State Of Origin the AFL has ever seen. Kernahan, Bradley and Platten take on Roos, Ablett and Frawley.

programme.title: Best Games Ever: 2016 QF HAW v GEE
programme.desc: 2016 Qualifying Final. Hawthorn and Geelong have been putting on classics for 30 years, and this one is no different, with a match that goes right down to, and beyond, the final siren.

programme.title: Best Games Ever: 1980 GF RIC v COL
programme.desc: 1980 Grand Final. Richmond v Collingwood. The biggest clubs meet on the biggest stage, and a legend is made as Kevin Bartlett saves his best for the last game of the year.

programme.title: Best Games Ever: 1993 R6 ESS v GEE
programme.desc: 1993 Round 6. At one end - Gary Ablett Senior. At the other - Paul Salmon. Those two alone would kick 24 goals that day in one of the great shootouts in AFL history.

programme.title: Best Games Ever: 2015 R16 ADE v PA
programme.desc: 2015 Round 16. The first Showdown after the loss of Crows coach Phil Walsh, this match was a rollercoaster of emotion from start to finish between Adelaide and Port Adelaide.

programme.title: Best Games Ever: 1990 QF COL v WCE
programme.desc: 1990 Qualifying Final. Magpie Peter Daicos did things with a footy no-one thought was possible. He goes deep into his bag of tricks against the Eagles to keep his premiership dream alive.

programme.title: Best Games Ever: 2012 R5 COL v ESS
programme.desc: 2012 Round 5. The Anzac Day clash between the Pies and the Bombers this year was an all-time great, as Dane Swan puts in a career game in front of a packed MCG.

programme.title: Best Games Ever: 2004 PF PA v STK
programme.desc: 2004 Preliminary Final. The Saints and the Power were a win away from a Grand Final - St Kilda's Fraser Gehrig kicked his 100th goal of the season mid-game which swung all the momentum.

programme.title: Best Games Ever: 2007 EF HAW v ADE
programme.desc: 2007 Elimination Final. Hawk Lance Franklin arrives as a genuine superstar, putting in a monster performance against the Crows on the September stage.

programme.title: Best Games Ever: 2019 PF COL v GWS
programme.desc: 2019 Preliminary Final. Footy's newest club - GWS, against one of the oldest - Collingwood. The last 5 minutes is as tense and gripping as any final in recent memory.

programme.title: Best Games Ever: 2013 QF GEE v FRE
programme.desc: 2013 Qualifying Final. The Cats get a true home final, forcing the Dockers to play at their Geelong fortress. It was controversial, but Freo showed up and took it right up to Geelong from the first bounce.

programme.title: Best Games Ever: 2004 R3 ESS v WCE
programme.desc: 2004 Round 3. James Hird is an icon, a legend of Essendon. Here he shows us why, with a performance in big moments that defined his career.

programme.title: Best Games Ever: 1997 PF WB v ADE
programme.desc: 1997 Preliminary Final. Preliminary finals are often decided by the smallest of margins - and that was the case in 1997 between the Dogs and the Crows.

programme.title: Best Games Ever: 1995 R4 COL v ESS
programme.desc: 1995 Round 4. The first ever ANZAC Day game between the Pies and the Bombers, and still one of the best ever played. Saverio Rocca kicks a bag in a thriller.

programme.title: Best Games Ever: 2000 R21 WB v ESS
programme.desc: 2000 Round 21. Essendon went into this game undefeated, and seemingly unstoppable. But the Dogs tried something new - a 'flood' - to try and upset the raging flag favourites.

programme.title: Best Games Ever: 1970 GF CAR v COL
programme.desc: 1970 Grand Final. The Pies were 44 points up against the Blues, and had one hand on the Premiership Cup. But Carlton weren't just going to hand the flag to their arch rival.

programme.title: Best Games Ever: 1984 GF ESS v HAW
programme.desc: 1984 Grand Final. Essendon and Hawthorn have spent generations hating each other, so when they meet on Grand Final day, all bets are off.

programme.title: Best Games Ever: 2014 PF HAW v PA
programme.desc: 2014 Preliminary Final. The Hawks are looking for back-to-back Premierships, but they need to get past the Power first. Port Adelaide show that they can match it with the reigning premier on footy's biggest stage.

programme.title: Best Games Ever: 2013 EF RIC v CAR
programme.desc: 2013 Elimination Final. Before the Tigers were a flag-winning franchise, they stumbled in September time and time again. In 2013 they met the Blues, who fell into the finals but weren't going to waste their shot.

programme.title: Best Games Ever: 2011 PF COL v HAW
programme.desc: 2011 Preliminary Final. The Pies were looking to go back-to-back, but Buddy and the Hawks had other plans. A prelim final with it all, including a finish no-one saw coming.

programme.title: AFL: R13 GEE v GC
programme.desc: Two of the hottest teams clash in Geelong where the Suns will be looking for their first win at the venue.

programme.title: AFL: R13 GWS v PA
programme.desc: The Giants are coming off two wins and will host Port Adelaide after a bye and looking to break a string of losses.

programme.title: AFL: R13 NM v WC
programme.desc: Both teams see this as one to win; the Roos fresh off the bye and the Eagles riding high from impressing the competition last week.

programme.title: AFLW: Grand Final NMT v BRI
programme.desc: Competition powerhouses North Melbourne and Brisbane clash in the AFLW Grand Final for the third year in a row at Ikon Park.

programme.title: Best Games Ever: 1993 PF ESS v ADE
programme.desc: 1993 Preliminary Final. The Crows had the Baby Bombers on the ropes to half time, before Kevin Sheedy's men click into gear in the second half.

programme.title: Best Games Ever: 2013 R13 BRI v GEE
programme.desc: 2013 Round 13. The Miracle on Grass. The Cats were cruising at the Gabba, but the Lions never, ever gave up - coming from 7 goals down to having a chance to win.

programme.title: Best Games Ever: 2001 R16 NM v ESS
programme.desc: 2001 Round 16. The Kangaroos were 10 goals up, but the Bombers rolled up their sleeves and got to work, closing the gap all the way to the final siren.

programme.title: Best Games Ever: 2002 GF BRI v COL
programme.desc: 2002 Grand Final. The Lions were looking at back-to-back flags. The Pies for their first since 1990. This brutal Grand Final would go down as one of the best of the modern era.

programme.title: Best Games Ever: 2005 SF SYD v GEE
programme.desc: 2005 Semi Final. Geelong head to the SCG to face the Swans in a scrappy, tense affair before a one-man last-quarter clinic blindsides us all.

programme.title: Best Games Ever: 2017 EF PA v WCE
programme.desc: 2017 Elimination Final. When the siren sounded, the Eagles and Power were tied. When the extra time siren sounded, they were tied. At the end of DOUBLE OVERTIME, they were still tied. It all hinges on a shot after the third final siren.

programme.title: Best Games Ever: 2008 GF HAW v GEE
programme.desc: 2008 Grand Final. The Cats at the peak of the powers against a Hawks side led by mastermind coach Alastair Clarkson, who called the Cats a 'shark' that couldn't breathe if it wasn't moving. A coaching move that started his legacy.

programme.title: Best Games Ever: 2009 R5 ESS v COL
programme.desc: 2009 Round 5. Anzac Day between the Bombers and the Pies. A wet afternoon at the G, it was a slog all day until David Zaharakis announced himself with seconds left in the game.

programme.title: Best Games Ever: 2009 GF GEE v STK
programme.desc: 2009 Grand Final. The Saints and the Cats were far and away the best teams of '09. And thy put on one of the best Grand Finals - a brutal tussle that was only broken by moments of sheer brilliance.

programme.title: Best Games Ever: 2012 GF HAW v SYD
programme.desc: 2012 Grand Final. This Grand Final had it all. Massive hits, blistering runs and moments that have lived forever in footy folklore on a perfect day in September.

programme.title: Best Games Ever: 2009 R14 STK v GEE
programme.desc: 2009 Round 14. The Cats and the Saints put on what is considered the best home-and-away game ever played. Blistering and brutal from start to finish it's two powerhouse teams at their peak going at it from siren to siren.

programme.title: Best Games Ever: 2013 PF GEE v HAW
programme.desc: 2013 Preliminary Final. The Hawks and the Cats - all they do is play in blockbusters. This one is no different as they fight tooth and nail for a spot in the 2013 Grand Final.

programme.title: Best Games Ever: 1999 PF ESS v CAR
programme.desc: 1999 Preliminary Final. The Bombers and the Blues duke it out on the MCG for the right to play in a Grand Final. A match that has gone down in footy folklore thanks to that tackle.

programme.title: Best Games Ever: 2006 GF SYD v WCE
programme.desc: 2006 Grand Final. Sydney and West Coast put on a Grand Final for the ages in 2005, and the very next year they did it again - going toe-to-toe until the bitter end.

programme.title: Best Games Ever: 2010 GF COL v STK
programme.desc: 2010 Grand Final. The Pies and the Saints meet on footy's biggest stage and put on a game that no-one will ever forget, where the bounce of the ball changed footy forever.

programme.title: Best Games Ever: 2005 GF SYD v WCE
programme.desc: 2005 Grand Final. Sydney and West Coast play off as the Swans aim to break the longest premiership drought in the AFL - 72 years.

programme.title: Best Games Ever: 2016 GF WB v SYD
programme.desc: 2016 Grand Final. The Bulldogs came from 7th to make a Grand Final in 2016, taking the hard road to face the Swans. Without their captain they must find one more big effort to break their premiership drought.

programme.title: Best Games Ever: 1989 GF GEE v HAW
programme.desc: 1989 Grand Final. Considered one of the best games ever played, this is a Grand Final everyone needs to watch at least once. Hits, hangers and highlights from start to finish in an old-school slugfest for a Premiership.

programme.title: Best Games Ever: 2016 PF GWS v WB
programme.desc: 2016 Preliminary Final. The Giants and the Dogs have a short, but fierce rivalry. Player defections, dirty tactics and high-stakes matches fuelled the fire for this one which didn't disappoint.

programme.title: Best Games Ever: 2018 GF COL v WCE
programme.desc: 2018 Grand Final. West Coast v Collingwood put on a frenetic Grand Final that hung in the balance until the dying seconds. History hinged on the smallest moments all day in a match that might be the best we've seen in the modern era.

programme.desc: Life imitates art when the cast and crew of a low-budget zombie flick start to turn into the living dead.

programme.title: The Parts You Lose
programme.desc: A young boy in a small North Dakota town befriends a potentially dangerous fugitive.

programme.title: The Wind
programme.desc: Lizzy is settling a remote stretch of land on the 19th-century American frontier, when she begins to sense a sinister presence that seems to be borne of the land itself.

programme.title: New Life
programme.desc: A mysterious woman on the run, and the resourceful fixer assigned to bring her in. Their two unique stories inextricably link, as the stakes of the pursuit rise to apocalyptic proportions.

programme.title: The Collector
programme.desc: As the seconds tick down to midnight, an ex-con becomes a reluctant hero trapped by a masked "Collector" in a maze of lethal invention while trying to rescue the very family he came to rob.

programme.title: A Tale of Two Sisters
programme.desc: On returning home from a mental health facility, two sisters find that, along with their stepmother, they have to find a way to deal with their late mother's ghost who begins to haunt them.

programme.title: Society
programme.desc: A Beverly Hills teen (Billy Warlock) discovers his parents are part of a gruesome orgy cult for the social elite.

programme.title: Sasquatch Sunset
programme.desc: In the misty forests of North America, a family of Sasquatches find themselves on a collision course with the ever-changing world around them.

programme.title: The Fall
programme.desc: A bedridden stuntman entrances a little girl with tales of exotic heroes. As his health reaches the point of peril so does the story he's telling, with dramatic consequences. An epic fantasy.

programme.title: Infernal Affairs
programme.desc: Chen Wing Yan, a young police officer, has been sent undercover as a mole in the local mafia. Lau Kin Ming, a young mafia member, infiltrates the police force.

programme.title: Vesper
programme.desc: Struggling to survive with her father after the collapse of Earth's ecosystem, 13-year-old Vesper must use her wits, strength and bio-hacking abilities to fight for the future.

programme.title: The Wild Goose Lake
programme.desc: On the run, gangster Zhou connects with sex worker Liu Aiai who was instructed to bring him in.

programme.title: The Crying Game
programme.desc: A reluctant IRA agent discovers that some people just aren't who you expect them to be.

programme.title: The Chaser
programme.desc: A cop investigates the disappearance of several call girls he pimps out.

programme.title: Jungle
programme.desc: An enthusiastic young adventurer follows his dreams into the Amazon jungle with two friends and a guide with a mysterious past.

programme.title: District B13: Ultimatum
programme.desc: Explosive sequel set in a futuristic Paris. Corrupt cops conspire to launch a nuclear strike and take over a ghetto terrorised by marauding drug gangs and killers. Subtitles.

programme.title: Howling IV: The Original Nightmare
programme.desc: A successful author moves to a small town after suffering a mental breakdown and is tormented by demons and werewolves.

programme.title: Dark Diamond
programme.desc: After his father's death, a man vows vengeance against the relatives who abandoned him.

programme.title: The Thicket
programme.desc: When a bounty hunter and a band of unlikely heroes pursue a brutal killer, they find themselves in a deadly no-man's-land known as the Thicket.

programme.title: Heathers
programme.desc: Veronica meets a James Dean-type newcomer who suggests they kill off the popular kids and end the cruel, unfair treatment the girls impose on unpopular kids at school.

programme.title: Good Boy
programme.desc: Christian, a millionaire heir, meets Sigrid, a young student, on a dating app. They hit it off, but there's only one problem: Christian lives with Frank, a man who dresses up and constantly acts like a dog.

programme.title: Police Story
programme.desc: A kung-fu policeman (Jackie Chan) must protect a female witness (Brigitte Lin) from a Hong Kong drug lord for whom she used to work.

programme.title: The Hit
programme.desc: A hit man is sent to Spain to kidnap an ex-criminal and transport him to Paris for execution.

programme.title: Joint Security Area
programme.desc: After a shooting incident at the North-South Korean border DMZ leaves two North Korean soldiers dead, a neutral Swiss and Swedish team investigates what actually happened.

programme.title: Prisoners Of The Ghostland
programme.desc: In the treacherous frontier city of Samurai Town, a notorious criminal must break an evil curse in order to rescue an abducted girl who has mysteriously disappeared.

programme.title: The Raid
programme.desc: A SWAT team is trapped in a tenement run by a ruthless mobster and his army of killers and thugs. Stranded on the sixth floor, they must fight their way through the city's worst to survive.

programme.title: Come To Daddy
programme.desc: Norval, a privileged man-child travels to the beautiful and remote cabin of his estranged father, in order to reconnect with him as he hasn't seen him in 30 years.

programme.title: Shutter
programme.desc: Late one night on a country road, Tun and Jane accidentally run over a mysterious pedestrian. Fleeing the scene, they return to their lives in Bangkok, but soon discover things have changed.

programme.title: Eyes Without a Face
programme.desc: A surgeon causes a car accident which leaves his daughter disfigured and goes to extreme lengths to give her a new face.

programme.title: District B13
programme.desc: Captain Damien must team up with Leito, a local insurgent from District 13, to defuse a neutron bomb that has fallen into the hands of a local drug lord, Taha, and rescue Leito's sister Lola.

programme.title: The Navigator: A Medieval Odyssey
programme.desc: A young 14th Century boy with acute psychic powers believes that he can rescue his fellow villagers by tunnelling their way through the earth. To their surprise they come out in New Zealand in 1988.

programme.title: Timecrimes
programme.desc: A man accidentally gets into a time machine and travels back in time nearly an hour. Finding himself will be the first of a series of disasters of unforeseeable consequences.

programme.title: To Catch a Killer
programme.desc: Detective Joe Kozenczak (Michael Riley) tracks down John Wayne Gacy (Brian Dennehy), convicted in 1980 of 33 Chicago serial killings.

programme.title: Amulet
programme.desc: An ex-soldier is offered a place to stay at a decaying house inhabited by a young woman and her dying mother. Falling for her, he suspects something sinister is going on.

programme.title: The Stunt man
programme.desc: A fugitive stumbles onto a movie set just when they need a new stunt man, takes the job as a way to hide out and falls for the leading lady while facing off with his manipulative director.

programme.title: Coming Home In The Dark
programme.desc: A school teacher is forced to confront a brutal act from his past when a pair of ruthless drifters takes him and his family on a nightmare road-trip.

programme.title: Hell House LLC II: The Abbadon Hotel
programme.desc: Eight years after a hotel's tragic opening, an investigative journalist is convinced key evidence remains in the abandoned hotel.

programme.title: Hellraiser III: Hell on Earth
programme.desc: J.P., a womanising nightclub owner, buys a bizarre, abstract pillar at a mysterious art gallery. Unknowingly, he's purchased the gateway to hell.

programme.title: The Texas Chain Saw Massacre
programme.desc: Teenagers are tortured, chopped up and impaled on meat hooks by a demented backwards family. This grisly 1974 blood-curdler ranks with Psycho and Halloween as a landmark in the horror/slasher genre.

programme.title: A Bittersweet Life
programme.desc: A gangster starts a violent feud after he refuses to kill his boss's cheating girlfriend.

programme.title: God is a Bullet
programme.desc: After his ex-wife is murdered and his daughter is kidnapped, Bob Hightower, infiltrates the group to hunt down their leader with the help of the cult's only female victim escapee.

programme.title: Bride of Re-Animator
programme.desc: A mad doctor and his accomplice return to the scene of a zombie massacre to continue their bodybuilding experiments.

programme.title: The Crying Game
programme.desc: A reluctant IRA agent discovers that some people just aren't who you expect them to be.

programme.title: Black Robe
programme.desc: In 1634 a Jesuit missionary sets out to convert the tribes in Huron Indian country. A culture-clashing masterpiece from Australian director Bruce Beresford.

programme.title: Top Knot Detective
programme.desc: Takashi Takamoto begins writing jingles for a well-known Japanese company and ends up creating a bloody series of samurai action that, over time, becomes a cult series.

programme.title: Children of the Corn
programme.desc: While driving through Nebraska two young lovers stumble upon a cult made up of murderous, demon-worshiping children. Based on a Stephen King horror story.

programme.title: Children of the Corn II: Final Sacrifice
programme.desc: When the mutilated bodies of adults are found in Nebraska no one believes that the killers could be children hiding in the cornfields. A journalist covering the story delves into the truth.

programme.title: Children of the Corn III: Urban Harvest
